BT 1 0 0 1 0 193 Tm 1.704531 Tw 13.5 TL /F2 9.5 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Core finding:) Tj /F1 9.5 Tf ( ChipOS is an independently developed, vendor-neutral semiconductor design platform) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.390431 Tw (owned by FutureAtoms. FutureAtoms operates across nine diverse domains: semiconductor design) Tj T* 0 Tw .201631 Tw (\(ChipOS\), healthcare \(Swaastik, targeting 150K+ facilities per FutureAtoms project specifications\), music) Tj T* 0 Tw .121831 Tw (generation \(BevyBeats\), professional networking AI \(Zaphy\), workflow automation \(Agentic Control\), RTL) Tj T* 0 Tw 6.062312 Tw (generation \(SystemVerilogGPT\), wellness \(Yuj\), mental health \(Savitri\), and computer vision) Tj T* 0 Tw .558629 Tw (\(AdaptiveVision\). This demonstrates that it is a broad technology platform, not a competitor to Axelera's) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.490109 Tw (hardware business. Wingman is an application built specifically for Axelera's Voyager SDK, delivered) Tj T* 0 Tw .582067 Tw (under a separate license. Wingman uses general development patterns and structural approaches from) Tj T* 0 Tw .721346 Tw (ChipOS \(as acknowledged in the counter-proposal's "Shared Development Patterns" provision\), but the) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.268982 Tw (two products are ) Tj /F2 9.5 Tf (independent of each other) Tj /F1 9.5 Tf (: separate repositories, separate databases, separate) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.859817 Tw (Docker networks, no runtime imports, and entirely different architectures. The shared developer and) Tj T* 0 Tw .140863 Tw (shared design patterns do not create employer IP claims over ChipOS, as any attempt to claim employer) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.122331 Tw (ownership through the employment relationship fails the cumulative test of Article 7 Auteurswet, as) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.68422 Tw (conditions \(2\) and \(3\) are not met \(condition \(1\), the existence of an employment relationship, is) Tj T* 0 Tw (conceded\).) Tj T* ET
